  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Banana Cream</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Dessert</cat></categories>
      <yield>4</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>75</qty>
          <unit>grams</unit></amt>
        <item>3 oz dried, no soak apricots</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Ripe bananas.</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>300</qty>
          <unit>grams</unit></amt>
        <item>10 oz low fat yogurt.</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Chop up the apricots and divide between four bowls. Puree the bananas with
  the yogurt in a blender. Divide the yogurt mixture between the bowls.
  
